        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The draft dust has barely settled in Washington, where a 5-12 stumble left the Commanders third in the NFC East - six games back, but armed with prime picks to rebuild around Jayden Daniels. <strong>Analyst Logan Paulsen's post-draft breakdown yesterday lit up the airwaves</strong>, hailing No. 7 overall snag Sonny Styles as a \"one-of-one\" freak - 6-foot-4, versatile enough to terrorize from linebacker or safety, unlocking Dan Quinn's defense like nobody since prime London Fletcher. They snagged six rookies total, bulking the backfield with sixth-round bruiser Kaytron Allen - a Penn State yardage machine already dubbed the Chris Rodriguez heir, poised to grind behind Rachaad White - and deepening lines everywhere from Chig Okonkwo at tight end to a crowded corner room. No splashy free-agency fireworks this offseason, but GM Adam Peters traded shrewdly for depth, eyeing Daniels' growth via technical trench help. It's a roster reset after that late win streak fizzled - competition everywhere, no handouts. <strong>Minicamp next week thrusts these kids into OTAs</strong>, where Styles' speed and Allen's hammer meet vets; fail to gel, and 2026's another slog - succeed, and the East quakes.",
